$ SAS: proc options
@ proc options

{ value

  Query the value of an → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options[option].

  gh|about-SAS|/programming/proc/options/value.sas||


  The value of an option can also be determined with the → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/functions/getoption[`getoption`] function.

}
{ Define an option and show its value

  gh|about-SAS|/programming/proc/options/value.sas||

}
{ config #proc-options-config

  Show which → Companies-Products/SAS/files/configuration[configuration files] were used when the system and/or session started up:
  gh|about-SAS|/programming/proc/options/config.sas||

}
{ groups

  SAS classifies options into groups. The group names can be queried with `listgroup`, the options belonging to a certain group can be queired with `group=GROUPNAME`:
  gh|about-SAS|/programming/proc/options/groups.sas||

}
{ Querying multiple options

  gh|about-SAS|/programming/proc/options/multiple.sas||

}
{ Querying restricted options

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/_restricted[Restricted options] can be queried with `proc options restrict; run;`.

}
{ Querying internal options

code {
proc options internal;
run;
code }

}

sa:


  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/proc
